<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The call may discard const-qualification: calculate_nonce declares saddr as const struct sockaddr_storage * but the call passes it to digest_update. If digest_update is prototyped as digest_update(struct DigestAlgorithm *da, void *data, size_t size) (i.e. the second parameter is a non-const pointer), then this call discards the const qualifier and thus violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13. If, however, digest_update is declared to take a const void * (e.g. digest_update(struct DigestAlgorithm *da, const void *data, size_t size)), there is no violation.
</scenario>

